# 3. Product Vision

IIS allows users to express infrastructure requirements without learning Terraform, HCL, CloudFormation, Pulumi, Kubernetes manifests, AWS CLI parameters, or the IIS syntax itself.

The primary user experience is:

```text
Natural-language requirement
        ↓
Intent understanding
        ↓
Clarification and completeness checks
        ↓
Structured draft intent
        ↓
Canonical Infrastructure Model
        ↓
Deterministic IIS serialization
        ↓
Schema and semantic validation
        ↓
Policy, security, cost and compliance analysis
        ↓
Provider mapping
        ↓
Deterministic execution plan
        ↓
Human approval
        ↓
Provider API execution
        ↓
State, verification and drift management
```

Example user request:

> Create a production-ready, highly available container platform in AWS with PostgreSQL, private networking, autoscaling, monitoring, encrypted backups, workload identity, and PCI DSS controls. Keep the estimated monthly infrastructure cost below $4,000.

The platform must convert this request into a valid `infrastructure.iis.yaml` document after asking only the questions that are genuinely required.

The user must not be required to understand IIS syntax.

