# 6. Authoring Methods

All authoring methods must produce or modify the same Canonical Infrastructure Model and serialize it into the same IIS document.

## 6.1 Natural language

This is the primary beginner workflow.

Support:

* Initial infrastructure creation
* Incremental changes
* Resource removal
* Constraint changes
* Environment cloning
* Cost reduction requests
* Security hardening requests
* Compliance requirements
* Explanations of proposed changes

Natural-language input must never directly mutate the IIS document. It must first produce structured compiler operations.

## 6.2 Guided UI

The visual application must support progressive disclosure.

### Basic mode

Expose outcome-oriented settings such as:

* Workload type
* Environment
* Expected usage
* Availability requirement
* Data classification
* Public or private exposure
* Scaling requirement
* Backup requirement
* Compliance requirement
* Cost budget
* Preferred geography

### Advanced mode

Expose the complete supported configuration surface for the selected provider mapping, including required and optional provider parameters.

Advanced settings must:

* Remain isolated in namespaced extensions
* Be validated against provider schemas
* Show provider documentation
* Show default values
* Explain operational and cost impact
* Warn when a setting weakens declared intent
* Never silently override core IIS requirements

## 6.3 IDE commands and assistant integration

Users must be able to create and modify infrastructure from:

* VS Code
* Cursor
* Claude Code
* Windsurf
* JetBrains IDEs
* Other MCP-capable or LSP-capable development environments

Example operations:

```text
Create infrastructure for this application
Add a private PostgreSQL database
Make this service highly available
Show the infrastructure architecture
Estimate the monthly cost
Explain the security risks
Generate a deployment plan
```

IDE assistants call IIS tools. They must not manipulate provider resources directly.

## 6.4 Direct IIS editing

Advanced users can edit `infrastructure.iis.yaml`.

Provide:

* JSON Schema validation
* LSP completion
* Hover documentation
* Formatting
* Diagnostics
* Quick fixes
* Relationship navigation
* Live diagrams
* Plan previews

