# 13. Definition of Done for Every Feature

A feature is not complete until:

* Its behavior is documented.
* Its public API is typed.
* It has unit tests.
* It has integration tests.
* It has at least one valid example.
* It has at least one invalid or failure example.
* It has security analysis.
* It has deterministic behavior tests where applicable.
* It has error codes.
* It has CLI or SDK exposure where relevant.
* It passes the conformance suite.
* It does not introduce provider concepts into the core.
* It does not place AI in the execution path.
* It is merged through a reviewed pull request.
* Roadmap status and evidence are updated.

