# 14. Prohibited Implementation Shortcuts

Do not:

* Generate Terraform as the main implementation.
* Use an LLM to execute AWS CLI commands.
* Treat generated YAML as trusted before validation.
* Make the visual UI the source of truth.
* Persist cloud credentials in IIS or state.
* Hide provider parameters from advanced users.
* Apply hidden defaults.
* Allow provider extensions to weaken core requirements silently.
* Use MCP output directly as execution input.
* Couple the core to AWS-specific concepts.
* Claim exact cost when only an estimate is available.
* Claim compliance certification from configuration checks.
* Promise universal rollback.
* Use document order as deployment order.
* Store architecture diagrams separately as authoritative data.
* Start enterprise UI development before the model, SDK, and planner are stable.
* proceed to a dependent phase while prerequisite exit criteria are failing.

